    "However, the corresponding physical Einstein radius",
    "increases with increasing distance.",
    "One further interpretation of θ E follows from rewriting Eq.",
    "Recalling that GM/ξ is the squared circular speed v 2 c at radius ξ we see that θ E is related to kinematics.",
    "A circular speed of 300 km s -1 corresponds to an Einstein radius of up to 4v 2 c /c 2 which is roughly an arcsecond."
